SUMMARY:Next Level Workshop  Discovering the Unexpected
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Move beyond your preconceptions into a state of authentic disc
 overy with collaborative masters Carol Mickett and Robert Stackhouse. Thro
 ugh a deliberately limited palette of materials\, you will engage in creat
 ing 48 quick artworks. This is not about perfection its about letting go o
 f control to uncover surprising moments of interest and meaning. Guided cr
 itiques throughout will help you recognize patterns\, break habits\, and r
 eframe your relationship to your own work. You will select one or two of y
 our 48 pieces to develop further. Leave with new work and renewed confiden
 ce in where the unexpected can lead! Ages 18  All Levels  All Supplies and
  lunch included. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/185956
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185956
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a12ed9b9-6919-4d72-924f-11e2543f0454
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260412T001102Z
DTSTART:20260411T140000Z
DTEND:20260411T153000Z
SUMMARY:Walking Tour: Downtown Tampa
LOCATION:400 N. Franklin St. Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a unique activity to do in Tampa Bay? Join the Tam
 pa Bay History Center for an immersive downtown walking tour. This guided 
 trek leads you past some of the citys most storied landmarks\, including C
 ity Hall\, Sacred Heart Church\, the Floridan Palace Hotel\, and The Hub\,
  Tampas oldest bar. Along the route\, your guide will share the stories th
 at connect these sites to the citys vibrant past. The tour lasts 90 minute
 s\, begins at 10 a.m.\, and is limited to 25 guests for a more personal ex
 perience. The route covers about one mile along sidewalks and brick street
 s\, so comfortable shoes and outdoor attire are recommended. Your starting
  point is Lykes Gaslight Park at 400 N. Franklin St.\, right in the center
  of downtown. Street parking is available nearby\, making it easy to begin
  your journey. Advance tickets are required\, and private tours can be boo
 ked by calling (813) 228-0097. Group size is small and tickets go fast. Re
 serve your spot today and experience downtown Tampa through the lens of hi
 story. Looking for other tours? Visit our walking tour page . \n\nPermalin
 k: https://www.tampa.gov/node/185851
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185851
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8cf6ccb1-ffe6-40d6-b354-6ed4055332c2
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260412T001102Z
DTSTART:20260411T130000Z
DTEND:20260411T200000Z
SUMMARY:2026 Spring Plant Festival
LOCATION:12210 USF Pine Drive Tampa \, FL 33612 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a two-day celebration of all things plants! The US
 F Botanical Gardens Spring Plant Festival brings together over 40 local gr
 owers\, rare and native plants\, artisan goods\, food trucks and family-fr
 iendly activities  all in the beautiful setting of the USF Botanical Garde
 ns. Whether youre an experienced gardener or just getting your hands dirty
  for the first time\, this is the perfect place to discover your next favo
 rite plant  and get expert advice while youre at it. Tickets Discounted ti
 ckets are available now for pre-sale  secure your spot today and skip the 
 line! Purchase Tickets Here Tickets will be sold at the door for 10 Festiv
 al Highlights Shop a wide selection of rare\, native\, and exotic plants C
 onnect with local growers and plant experts Browse artisan vendors with ha
 ndcrafted goods Enjoy delicious eats from Tampas best food trucks Bring yo
 ur furry friend (on a leash) Create memories with fun activities for the w
 hole family Event Details Dates: April 11  12\, 2026 Time: 9 a.m.  3 p.m. 
 Membership early access at 8:30 a.m . Location: USF Botanical Gardens 1221
 0 USF Pine Drive\, Tampa\, FL 33612 Accessibility Visitor parking availabl
 e on-site  Handicap parking available along USF Pine Drive Plant Pick-Up A
 rea located next to the admission tents Please note: The BullRunner shuttl
 e will NOT be in service during the event Accessibility Accommodations or 
 Questions? The USF Botanical Gardens is committed to providing an inclusiv
 e and accessible experience for all guests. If you require reasonable acco
 mmodations or have any questions\, please contact us at botanicalgardensus
 f.edu (mailto:cas-rsvpusf.edu?subjectFall20Festival20Accessibility20Concer
 ns) before the event. All dogs and small pets on leashes are welcome! Dont
  miss this beloved spring tradition! Come for the plants  stay for the peo
 ple\, food\, and inspiration. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/18
 7631
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187631
END:VEVENT
